  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Describe the feature you would like\n\nRecently, we've merged https://github.com/gakonst/foundry/pull/201 with basic formatter functionality which includes:\r\n- Parsing source code (respecting project structure) with [solang](https://github.com/hyperledger-labs/solang/)\r\n- Traversing the Parse Tree and reconstructing the code on-the-go\r\n- Reconstructing some basic nodes such as pragma directives, import directives and enum definitions\r\n\r\nThe caveat is that we've disabled `forge fmt` CLI command for now because it doesn't preserve every piece of original code: comments are missing. Solang recently added support for parsing regular comments: https://github.com/hyperledger-labs/solang/pull/656. All we need to do now is to support it in our formatter.\r\n\r\nThe hard part about it is that regular comments, in contrast to NatSpec ones, can appear everywhere, so we need to keep that in mind.\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
