    "body": "comments are not part of the AST right? this makes it significantly harder to traverse the tree and simply to node -> text.\r\n\r\nSo I guess we need to find a way to inject them somehow. \r\nthis is a bit tricky because we need to check at every node if there's a comment.\r\n\r\n~~one idea I have is, to write an additional CommentVisitor that wraps the actual visitor and before delegating to the wrapped visitor, checks if there's comment before the node.~~\r\n\r\nperhaps we can solve this with a macro that we add in every visit function, that checks if the next comment's location is before the location of current node, if so visit_comment?\r\n\r\n",
